other_tests.findings: Diagnosis of renal-cell carcinoma confirmed, a roughly spherical 10.5-cm well-circumscribed mass that was confined to the kidney with no invasion of adjacent fat or vasculature and negative resection margins.
other_tests.changes_over_time: The patient is doing well, with no evidence of recurrent disease or metastasis on surveillance imaging 2 years post-surgery.

other_tests.findings: No mutations found in VHL, MET, FH, FLCN, SDH, TSC1/2, PTEN, MITF, BAP1, CDKN2B, or PBRM1 genes; germline variants of unknown significance found in KPR1B, GPR124, PDGFRA, SF3B1, FGFR4, JAK2 genes.
